snippet: Fifty-four vessels started off Thursday from Port Townsend, Wash., in the 750-mile event. To the winner goes $10,000; to second place, steak knives.
abstract: Inaugural Race to Alaska, 750-mile boating contest from Port Townsend, Wash, to Ketchikan, Alaska, is being billed as one-of-a-kind event; organizers say anything goes in getting from Point A to Point B, as long as vessel is human powered, with no support teams and no burning of gas.
lead_paragraph: Fifty-four vessels started off Thursday from Port Townsend, Wash., in the 750-mile event. To the winner goes $10,000; to second place, steak knives.

headline.main: A Race to Alaska: No Motors, but No Limits on Imagination
headline.print_headline: 54 Contenders Run on Ideas, Not Engines
